    Federal Judicial
   The judicial branch hears cases that challenge or require
   interpretation of the legislation passed by Congress and signed by the
   President. It consists of the U. S. Supreme Court and the lower federal
   courts.
   When you click on a link below you will leave this site and go to
   another Federal Government website.
     * Supreme Court of the United States
     * U.S. Judicial Circuit Courts of Appeal, by Geographic Location and
       Circuit
     * U.S. Court of Appeals for the Federal Circuit
     * U.S. Court of Federal Claims
     * U.S. Court of Appeals for the Armed Forces
     * U.S. Court of Appeals for Veterans Claims
     * U.S. Tax Court
     * U.S. Court of International Trade
     * The U.S Federal Courts: The Federal Judiciary homepage from the
       Administrative Office of the U.S. Courts
     * U.S. Sentencing Commission
     * Federal Judicial Center
     * U.S. Code
     * Online Opinions and Court Records

     * Public Access to Court Electronic Records (PACER) for U.S.
       District, Bankruptcy and Appellate court records
     * Online Opinions for DC Circuit
     * Online Opinions for Federal Circuit
     * Online Opinions for all U.S. Circuit Courts via FindLaw

